CatDescriptText: Mrs. Irene Brown, housewife, Sheraden, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in the Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, January 6, 1962, pg.7 with question: "What goal or goals should the Pittsburgh Negro aim for in 1962?" answer reads: "They should try to better themselves and participate in helping out in the various organizations that are trying to get better jobs."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Irene Brown wearing floral head scarf and dark coat with fur collar, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown; Three quarter portrait of man wearing dark fedora and light colored coat buttoned to neck, standing in front of Bud Saunders Flowers, Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
